  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Peel and chop your<strong> sweet potato[es]</strong> into wedges</p><p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578934362492-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578934362492-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578934362492-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578934362492-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1578934362492-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>sweet potato wedges</strong> to one side of a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> to the other side of the tray (or use a separate tray!) with your <strong>soy sauce</strong> and a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and give it a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray[s] in the oven for 20 min or until the sweet potato is cooked through and tender and the chickpeas are starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578934369197-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578934369197-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578934369197-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578934369197-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1578934369197-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>bulgur wheat</strong> and <strong>dried cranberries</strong> to a pot with plenty of <strong>boiled water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 7-9 min or until tender with a slight bite</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578934373699-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578934373699-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578934373699-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578934373699-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1578934373699-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>cumin seeds</strong> to the pan</p><p>Toast for 1-2 min or until fragrant, then transfer the <strong>toasted seeds</strong> to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and bash to a fine powder</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578934380342-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578934380342-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578934380342-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578934380342-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1578934380342-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, peel and roughly chop your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Cut your <strong>green chilli[es]</strong> in half lengthways, deseed (scrape the seeds out with a teaspoon) and chop finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Cut your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> in half</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578934389847-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578934389847-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578934389847-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578934389847-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1578934389847-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>(not a big garlic fan? Try using less!), <strong>chopped chilli </strong>(can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and <strong>coriander </strong>to the <strong>pestle & mortar </strong>with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and grind to a paste</p><p>Add 3 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[4 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[6 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and the<strong> </strong>juice of <strong>half</strong> your<strong> lemon[s]</strong> and stir it all together – this is your <strong>zhoug</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578934395191-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578934395191-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578934395191-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578934395191-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1578934395191-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>pistachios</strong> and <strong>flaked almonds</strong> to a separate baking tray and put in the oven for 2-3 min or until golden and toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Once toasted, roughly chop the <strong>pistachios </strong>(Careful they may be hot!)</p><p>Add<strong> half</strong> of the<strong> chopped pistachios</strong> and <strong>flaked almonds</strong> (save the rest for garnish!) to the <strong>cooked bulgur</strong> with the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>jewelled bulgur</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578934400553-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578934400553-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578934400553-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578934400553-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-7-1578934400553-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> roasted sweet potato</strong> and <strong>crispy chickpeas</strong> over the <strong>jewelled bulgur</strong></p><p>Drizzle over the<strong> zhoug</strong> and garnish with the <strong>remaining nuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
